        "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go",
        "goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ConstructWifiInfo` returns no error and exits early on several failure-like states (nil service/state, unresolved device), so callers cannot distinguish success from skipped refresh.",
        "Adjacent APIs (`IsWifiEnabled`, `ListWifiSSIDs`, `ConnectToWifi`, `DisconnectWifi`, `ToggleDevice`) explicitly return wrapped errors for comparable runtime precondition failures."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Return an error from `ConstructWifiInfo` (or a status enum) and propagate device-resolution/runtime precondition failures so WiFi API callers observe a consistent failure contract.",
